      "text": [
        " اسْتَوَى مِنْ كُلِّ شَيْ‏ءٍ فَلَيْسَ شَيْ‏ءٌ أَقْرَبَ إِلَيْهِ مِنْ شَيْ‏ءٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "And by this chain, from Sahl, from Al Hassan Bin Mahboub, from Muhamad Bin Marid, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> was asked about the Words of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic <span class=\"ibTxt\"><a href=\"/#/books/quran:20#h5\"><a href=\"/books/quran:20#h5\">[20:5]</a></a> The Beneficent is Even upon the Throne</span>. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Even from everything. So there isn’t anything closer to Him<sup>azwj</sup> than a (another) thing’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          " 7. Sahl through the same chain of narrators has narrated from al-Hassan ibn Mahbub from Maridin the following. “A person asked Imam abu ‘Abdallah about the words of Allah, “The Beneficent God is dominant over the Throne (of the realm) <a href=\"/#/books/quran:20#h5\"><a href=\"/books/quran:20#h5\">[20:5]</a></a>.” The Imam said, “He established His control in all things."
        ]
      }
    },
